<HEADLINE>
 
</HEADLINE>
  (For use by New York Times News Service clients) 
  
<TEXT>
<P>
   The following Arizona Republic story has been added for use by
clients of the NYTimes News Service for Thursday, March 25. If you
have any questions, please contact the Republic News Desk at (602)
444-8286.
</P>
<P>
   &QL; 
MEDICAL-DEATH _ A Mesa doctor denied Wednesday that he refused to
treat a 13-year-old girl who died hours later of a ruptured
appendix. As hundreds of people poured out their support and expre
ssed outrage over the death of Gricelda Zamora, Dr. Stuart Agren,
in a written statement, said Gricelda did not appear critically ill
when she came into his office last Thursday, and had been at a
hospital emergency room only minutes before. Story will move in the
``A'' category. &QL;
</P>
