   The alliance's refusal to listen to Moscow's pleas to spare its
Slavic cousins in Serbia marks a new low in an increasingly
ambivalent relationship with the United States, in which Russia _
to its horror _ finds itself cast not so much an enemy as a
sponging lightweight.
</P>
