<SLUG> BC-HKN-DUCKS-LADN </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
DUCKS' TRADE FOR ZEZEL NULLIFIED
</HEADLINE>
 (For use by NYTimes News Service clients) 
By GREG CHRISTENSEN  
 San Gabriel Valley Tribune  
<TEXT>
<P>
   ANAHEIM, Calif. _ The harsh reality of life superseeded hockey
on Wednesday when the Anaheim Mighty Ducks' trade for Peter Zezel
was nulified.
</P>
<P>
   Zezel chose not report to Anaheim so he could remain in Toronto
with his 3{-year-old niece, Julliann Carter, who is dying of
neuroblastoma -- a malignant tumor.
</P>
<P>
   The 33-year-old center, who the Ducks acquired from Vancouver on
Tuesday, will not return to the Canucks this season. He will likely
forfeit the remainder of his $800,000 contract. Zezel becomes a
free agent this summer.
</P>
<P>
   ``Any other time I'd have loved to go play for Anaheim, said
Zezel, who reportedly asked Vancouver not to trade him. ``But if
I'm not with my family through this I will regret it the rest of my
life.
</P>
<P>
   Zezel's sister's daughter was diagnosed in Feb. 98 and six weeks
ago was given just weeks to live.
</P>
<P>
   ``She is day-to-day, she could pass away tommorrow, Zezel told
the Vancouver Province.
</P>
<P>
   Earlier this season, while Zezel was recovering from a foot
injury, he took a one-week leave of absence to take his niece to
Disneyworld.
</P>
<P>
   The Ducks will be returned the eighth-round draft pick they sent
to Vancouver for Zezel.
</P>
<P>
   ``He said he his mind wasn't into it and I said `ok' , said
Anaheim general manager Pierre Gauthier. ``We wanted a little depth
and veteran leadership. It's unfortunate he's not coming, but
there's a legitimate reason.
</P>
<P>
   The GM added: ``There is nobody to blame. It's a unique
situation. There is a human factor we can do nothing about.
</P>
</TEXT>
