<P>
   WASHINGTON NEWS (``w'' category)
</P>
<P>
   KOSOVO-HISTORY (Washington) _ With its barren hills and poor
villages, Kosovo appears an unlikely place for Yugoslav President
Slobodan Milosevic to make his stand against the West and risk
punishing NATO air strikes. But to Serbian nationalists, a bitter
history spanning 600 years has raised Kosovo's cultural importance
to that of Jerusalem for Christians and Jews. By MARK HELM.
</P>
<P>
   COMMENTARY (``k'' category)
</P>
<P>
   MEANS-COLUMN (Washington) _ If all the Republican presidential
candidates pledge to name only justices who promise they'll vote to
overturn Roe v. Wade _ as anti-abortion forces are demanding _ the
concepts of separation of powers and judicial integrity will be
dangerously compromised. By MARIANNE MEANS.
</P>
