   BKN-KNICKS (Sacramento, Calif.) _ Folo on the Knicks'
last-second loss Wednesday to the Kings, the latest in what is
becoming a substantial list of games in which New York has the lead
in the fourth quarter, gives it away, and then misses a final shot
to tie or win the game. They are still above .500, at 15-13, but
there is clearly an uncomfortable feeling surrounding the team. By
Selena Roberts.
</P>
