</P>
<P>
   HKN-RANGERS (Miami) _ Folo on the Rangers, who came up with a
nice road victory over the Panthers on Wednesday night but still
remain 5 points out of a playoff spot in an increasingly hopeless
situation. By Joe LaPointe.
</P>
<P>
   HKN-DEVILS-PENGUINS (East Rutherford, N.J.) _ Pittsburgh at
Devils, 7:30 p.m.
</P>
<P>
   BKC-SCOONIE-PENN (Undated) _ Feature on Scoonie Penn, the very
talented point guard of Ohio State and a player who followed his
coach from Boston College to the Buckeyes. By Lauren Battista.
</P>
<P>
   BKW-FINAL-FOUR (San Jose, Calif.) _ Advancing the women's Final
Four NCAA showdown, which takes place Friday night. It's Duke vs.
Georgia and Purdue vs. Louisiana Tech. By Bill Pennington.
</P>
<P>
   TENN-LIPTON (Key Biscayne, Fla.) _ The women are dominating the
Lipton Championships. Today's quartfinal doubleheader is Graf vs.
Davenport and Venus Williams vs. Novotna. By Robin Finn.
</P>
<P>
   BOX-TV (Undated) _ Eventually, Time Warner will make a deal to
carry Evander Holyfield-Lennox Lewis II on TVKO. That's inevitable.
Through TVKO and HBO, Time Warner has too much tied up in boxing to
use the stench of the March 13 draw as an excuse to exit the
proceedings. By Richard Sandomir.
</P>
