murder charge on Thursday against Dr. Jack Kevorkian after a
prosecutor told them the euthanasia crusader killed Thomas Youk
``like a medical hitman in the night with a bag of poison.''
Kevorkian, who was acting as his own attorney, likened himself to
civil rights heroes Rosa Parks and the Rev. Martin Luther King, and
insisted that his helping to kill the victim of Lou Gehrig's
disease was not a crime. By Pam Belluck.
</P>
