<P>
   MATZO-PRICES _ Once again, you can get a box of matzo for your
Passover celebration for $11.99. Or, you can hop a plane to Jersey
and buy a box for $4.99. But Bob Butterworth, Florida attorney
general, has looked into the matter and blames a variety of other
factors, but not collusion. (Sedore, Palm Beach Post)
</P>
<P>
   NORRELL _ ATLANTA _ Norrell Corp., the temporary employment
service founded by former gubernatorial candidate Guy Millner, is
sold to Interim Services of Fort Lauderdale for an estimated $553
million in stock. The combined company, with $4 billion in revenue,
will rank as as the industry's third-largest temporary employment
firm in revenue, according to Interim. (Atlanta
Journal-Constitution)
</P>
<P>
   DELTA _ ATLANTA _ The first of 13 custom Boeing 777s from an
order valued at more than $1.4 billion arrives at Delta Friday. For
more than a year, Delta has worked with the manufacturer to develop
the new wide-body flagship, which has been designed exclusively
with the airline's long-haul passengers in mind. Delta Ship7001 is
the first 777 with the BusinessElite cabin with 52 seats for
premium passengers. Not only has Delta introduced the first
intercontinental business class with five feet of space between its
sleeper seats, it has also taken the unusual step of choosing a
two-by-two configuration in the premium cabin of the 777 with no
middle seats. (Thurston, Atlanta Journal-Constitution) TENTATIVE
</P>
<P>
   DELTA-SELL _ ATLANTA _ Delta sells 119 Pratt &AMP; Whitney
JT8D-15/15A-powered Boeing 727-200s and up to 39 spare engines over
the next six years to a United Technologies unit. The equipment is
being retired from Delta's fleet. This is the largest used aircraft
fleet transaction. (Thurston, Atlanta Journal-Constitution)
</P>
<P>
   Story Filed By Cox Newspapers
</P>
