   COXNET NASCAR PAGE
</P>
<P>
   Eds: Here is the lineup for this week's COXNET NASCAR page. The
page will be available by 3 p.m. EST on Thursday. If you have any
questions, please call the CoxNet desk in Atlanta at 404 526-5456.
</P>
<P>
   CAR-WALTRIP _ The rocky road continues for Darrell Waltrip.
Waltrip, who was black-flagged at Darlington for going too slow, is
out of provisionals and will have to post a qualifying speed to
make the field at Texas. (Schlabach, Atlanta Journal-Constitution).
15.
</P>
<P>
   WITH
</P>
<P>
   CAR-NASCAR-ITEMS _ Odds/ends package. (Schlabach, Atlanta
Journal-Constitution). 18.
</P>
<P>
   CAR-WINSTON-NOTES _ Winston/Busch notes package. (Schlabach,
Atlanta Journal-Constitution).
</P>
<P>
   BASEBALL
</P>
<P>
   BBN-BRAVES-AJONES _ LAKE BUENA VISTA, Fla. _ It's safe to say
that Andruw Jones is enjoying this spring much more than last. One
year ago, the Braves were trying to turn Jones into a leadoff
hitter. It was an experiment that would fail miserably. (Rogers,
Atlanta Journal-Constitution). 13. MOVED
</P>
<P>
   COLLEGE BASKETBALL
</P>
<P>
   NCAA MEN'S TOURNAMENT
</P>
<P>
   BKC-COACHK _ ST. PETERSBURG, Fla. _ It's not a surprise that
Duke is competing in the Final Four this weekend considering that
the Blue Devils have been favored to win the national title since
the beginning of the season. However, it was only four seasons ago
that the Duke program was in disarray after Coach Mike Krzyzewski
missed most of the season following back surgery, the team finished
with a losing record and recruiting appeared to be down. But
recruiting efforts over the last four years have landed several
prep All-Americans and the Devils are back in the Final Four for
the first time since 1994. Now, they hope to complete their goal of
winning the national title. (Barnhart, Atlanta
Journal-Constitution). 25.
</P>
<P>
   WITH
</P>
<P>
   BKC-FINALFOUR-NOTES _ ST. PETERSBURG, Fla. _ NCAA men's
tournament notebook. (Barnhart, Atlanta Journal-Constitution). 18.
</P>
<P>
   BKC-UCONN-CALHOUN _ ST. PETERSBURG, Fla. _ A feature story on
UConn, most likely focusing on head coach Jim Calhoun making his
First Final Four and/or the Huskies backcourt. (Vinella, Dayton
Daily News).15.
</P>
<P>
   WITH
</P>
<P>
   BKC-OHIOST-NOTES _ ST. PETERSBURG, Fla. _ Ohio State NCAA
notebook. (Vinella, Dayton Daily News).10-12.
</P>
<P>
   NCAA WOMEN'S TOURNAMENT
</P>
<P>
   BKC-UGAWOMEN _ SAN JOSE, Calif. _ It's a bit of a surprise that
the Georgia Lady Dogs have advanced to the women's Final Four.
There's only one senior on the team and it's the same team that was
eliminated in the second round of the tournament last season. Also,
the team spent last summer wondering if coach Andy Landers was
leaving to accept a job in the WNBA. Landers declined, returned to
Athens and has led Georgia to its fifth Final Four appearance in
his 20 seasons. Georgia thought that next season might be its best
with the Miller twins as juniors, but the future is now as the team
is only two wins away from the national title. (Parker, Atlanta
Journal-Constitution). 25.
</P>
<P>
   BKC-UGA-DUKE _ SAN JOSE, Calif. _ Advancing the Georgia women
vs. Duke. (Parker, Atlanta Journal-Constitution). 12.
</P>
<P>
   BKC-DUKEWOMEN _ Women's Final Four advance on Duke women, who
can play the game, too. Just ask Tennessee. (Rosenberg, Palm Beach
Post)
</P>
<P>
   BKC-NCAA-WOMENNOTES _ SAN JOSE, Calif. _ NCAA women's tournament
notebook. (Parker, Atlanta Journal-Constitution). 18.
</P>
