   BKC-UGAWOMEN _ SAN JOSE, Calif. _ It's a bit of a surprise that
the Georgia Lady Dogs have advanced to the women's Final Four.
There's only one senior on the team and it's the same team that was
eliminated in the second round of the tournament last season. Also,
the team spent last summer wondering if coach Andy Landers was
leaving to accept a job in the WNBA. Landers declined, returned to
Athens and has led Georgia to its fifth Final Four appearance in
his 20 seasons. Georgia thought that next season might be its best
with the Miller twins as juniors, but the future is now as the team
is only two wins away from the national title. (Parker, Atlanta
Journal-Constitution). 25.
