<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-MOD-SQUAD-FILM-REVIEW-NYT </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
`THE MOD SQUAD': SQUAD THAT WAS MOD IS RESHOD
</HEADLINE>
  (editors: production notes at end of review)  
 (bl)  
 By LAWRENCE VAN GELDER   
 c.1999 N.Y. Times News Service    
<TEXT>
<P>
   When P.T. Barnum said, ``There's a sucker born every minute,''
he might have been anticipating the moviegoers who will pay as much
as $9.50 to see the torturously boring ``The Mod Squad.''
</P>
<P>
   Devoid of original plotting or suspense, clumsy in exposition,
reliant on ponderous music to underline its attempts to portray
action, played by unbelievable principals and ill-defined
subsidiary characters forced to mouth dull dialogue that reaches
the ridiculous, ``The Mod Squad'' is a film of unusual ineptitude.
</P>
<P>
   The main mystery surrounding this film (derived from an ABC
television series that ran from September 1968 to August 1973) is
why it was made. The precise culture and counterculture that
spawned the TV show are long past, and a tale of lawbreaking young
people given a second chance as members of a special youth squad of
police officers no longer resonates as it did in that turbulent
era.
</P>
<P>
   But even on its own terms, the movie ``The Mod Squad,'' directed
by Scott Silver and written by Silver, Stephen Kay and Kate Lanier,
is a notable failure.
</P>
<P>
   Just for the record, the unfortunate stars, introduced by
credits that seem likely to finish at about the same time as the
film does, are Claire Danes as Julie, Giovanni Ribisi as Pete and
Omar Epps as Linc. The three, saved from jail terms by Dennis
Farina as Adam Greer, a tough but kindly police captain, work
undercover in places like clubs and bars, where their youth
constitutes camouflage.
</P>
<P>
   But few of the police officers besides Greer find the youngsters
tolerable. When the film begins, a lot of cocaine is missing from a
police evidence locker, and the mod squad is sent into a club
suspected of being a link to prostitution. Before long, Greer is
dead, and the leaderless, unpopular mod squad is on its own in an
investigation into murder and police corruption.
</P>
<P>
   At the end, theater exit signs are welcome beacons.
</P>
<P>
   PRODUCTION NOTES:
</P>
<P>
   `THE MOD SQUAD'
</P>
<P>
   Directed by Scott Silver; written by Stephen Kay, Silver and
Kate Lanier, based on characters created by Buddy Ruskin; director
of photography, Ellen Kuras; edited by Dorian Harris; music by B.C.
Smith; production designer, Patrick Sherman; produced by Ben Myron,
Alan Riche and Tony Ludwig; released by Metro-Goldwyn-Mayer
Pictures.
</P>
<P>
   Cast: Claire Danes (Julie), Giovanni Ribisi (Pete), Omar Epps
(Linc), Dennis Farina (Greer), Josh Brolin (Billy), Michael Lerner
(Howard) and Steve Harris (Briggs).
</P>
<P>
   Running time: 94 minutes.
</P>
<P>
   Rating: ``The Mod Squad'' is rated R (Under 17 requires
accompanying parent or adult guardian). It involves violence,
simulated sex and impolite language.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
