 &QL; 
GOMEZ-COLUMN-2 (Havana, Cuba) - The rays of morning light splashing
against this city's landscape offered a far different view to
Havana than nightfall had managed to disguise just hours earlier.
</P>
<P>
   Havana's dim night lights _ make no mistake, this is a dark city
at night _ provided an unyielding mask to its scars and ills that
daylight simply could not conceal. Baseball columnist Pedro Gomez,
a first-generation Cuban-American, describes his impressions of his
parents' homeland. He is in Havana for Sunday's historic exhibition
game between the Baltimore Orioles and the Cuban National Team. By
PEDRO GOMEZ. Story moved in the ``A'' category. &QL; 
