<P>
   (Phoenix) - For the first time, President Clinton found himself
confronting the inglorious consequences of his most disgraceful
public act. Will the Clinton legacy ``be about lying?'' he was
asked at his first press conference since the awful cacophony of
the impeachment and Lewinsky scandals began. You can't really blame
the president for grasping at whatever straw may rescue his
heritage, but the plain fact is, his ``one negative'' constituted
one of the greatest whoppers of all time. Story moved in the ``K''
category. &QL; 
 &QL; 
EDIT-NATO GAMBLE (Phoenix) - President Clinton and NATO are betting
_ hoping, really _ that the launching of airstrikes will force
Yugoslav President Slobodan Milosevic to halt his killing and
aggression. In raising the stakes in Kosovo, it is not at all clear
whether America can achieve its aims without paying some high
costs. But by keeping channels of communication open with
Milosevic, it may still be possible to reach an agreement without
too much bloodshed. &QL;
