<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-LEAH-PERSONALS-SFCHRON </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
EAT YOUR HEART OUT, BUSTER SIMPSON
</HEADLINE>
  
 (Eds: This story also moved in the ``a'' national news file)  
 By LEAH GARCHIK  
 c.1999 San Francisco Chronicle
<TEXT>
<P>
   While prominent San Franciscans argue to and fro over the merits
of  &UR; Buster Simpson &LR; 's giant foot, a sculpture by local artist
 &UR; Michel Willaume &LR; , ``Awakening of the Springtime,'' has taken first
place in a national competition.
</P>
<P>
   ``The 45-pound piece is an image of a male figure evolving from
a tree with his hands half-open, releasing a hummingbird to the
sky,'' says an official description of the prizewinner. The work,
``which symbolizes the arrival and rebirth of spring, is a personal
adaptation of artist  &UR; Richard McDonald &LR; 's bronze sculpture entitled
`Butterfly.' `The floral composition represents springtime
vegetation,' explains Willaume. `The tree man's emergence from the
earth is an announcement of the new season and the melted snow at
the base represents the end of winter.' ''
</P>
<P>
   Willaume, whose sculpture, in chocolate, has earned him the
Pastry Chef of the Year title in the 20th Annual Patisfrance U.S.
Pastry Competition, is executive pastry chef at the Ritz-Carlton.
</P>
<P>
   As an expression of support for the arts, we suggest that all
future works of public art be created out of chocolate, consumed by
passers-by and replaced when gone.
</P>
<P>
   &QL;
</P>
<P>
   &UR; ULTRA-FLASH &LR;
</P>
<P>
   &UR; Gary Hanauer &LR;  sends word of the Bay Area Naturists' Tax Day
celebration, on April 17 at Gray Whale Cove near Devil's Slide. By
the 17th, says the group's newsletter, ``most of us will have come
to realize that the Internal Revenue Service just got the shirts
off our backs. So we might as well ditch everything else, too, and
just enjoy the freedom.''
</P>
<P>
   P.S. In related news,  &UR; Dianne Hales &LR; ' new book, ``Just Like a
Woman: How Gender Science Is Redefining What Makes Us Female''
(Bantam; $24.95), cites surveys that say the men to whom women are
most attracted are symmetrical. ``Women tend to choose partners who
are literally well balanced. ... This evolutionary bonus may
explain why the most symmetrical men _ in studies involving precise
measurements of virtually every body part _ report having three
times as many sex partners as their more lopsided peers.''
</P>
<P>
   &QL;
</P>
<P>
   &UR; SLOGANS, MOTTOS AND OFFICIAL MANTRAS &LR;
</P>
<P>
   ``United rising'' is the new United Airlines slogan, which
leaves adman  &UR; Kent Carthey &LR;  wondering about the alternatives.
Meanwhile, a handout noting that Ms. magazine is going back on
newsstands begins with the overaroused message ``Wake Up and Smell
the Estrogen.''
</P>
<P>
   In related news, a notice from I Love You International is
headlined, ``Want a Russian bride? Just click the mouse.''
</P>
<P>
   And when  &UR; Gene Marine &LR;  chose ``paper'' at Safeway, he got a sack
imprinted with a notice saying it was brought to him by the Vallejo
City Unified School District. The message: ``Your child will not
excel if they do not attend.''
</P>
<P>
   &UR; Margaret Barrett &LR;  received an official letter from the San
Francisco city controller's office with a preprinted return address
that placed it in San Frnacosco. And you know you're in San
Frnacosco when you're walking along Bryant Street between 2nd and
3rd, as  &UR; Betsy Bozdech &LR;  did, and you see etched into the sidewalk
cement, ``Yahoo sux!''
</P>
<P>
   &QL;
</P>
<P>
   &UR; FLASH &LR;
</P>
<P>
   &UR; _ George Lucas &LR;  has donated $1.5 million to his alma mater, the
University of Southern California, to create a new digital film
studio, to be named after  &UR; Akira Kurosawa &LR; . ``We pay tribute to
Kurosawa while at the same time inspiring students to break new
ground the way he did,'' said Lucas.
</P>
<P>
   _ Researchers at the University of Kentucky have figured out a
way to make Viagra a nasal spray, which, requiring no time to break
down in the stomach to make its way into the bloodstream, would
work almost immediately. A Pfizer spokeswoman told Men's Journal
that the company has no plans to market the speeded-up drug.
</P>
<P>
   ``We think people are putting that time to good use,''
 &UR; Mariann Caprino &LR;  said.
</P>
<P>
   _  &UR; Jimmy &LR;  and  &UR; Rosalynn Carter &LR;  are building houses in the
Philippines, accompanied by 2,000 volunteers with Habitat for
Humanity. They hope to build 293 homes in a week.
</P>
<P>
   &QL;
</P>
<P>
   &UR; WHO SAID WHAT &LR;
</P>
<P>
   ``Madonna's hair is such a problem for me, for her &LR;  and for her
millions of fans.''
</P>
<P>
   _ Gossipist Liz Smith in the New York Observer.
</P>
</TEXT>
