   (NYT24) NEW YORK -- March 25, 1999 -- KOSOVO-VOICES-3, 3-25 -- A
woman blesses herself at the Serbian Orthodox Cathedral in lower
Manhattan on Thursday. A special service was held at the church in
memory of those who were killed or injured in NATO's bombing of
Yugoslavia. (Frances Roberts/New York Times Photo)
</P>
<P>
   (NYT23) NEW YORK -- March 25, 1999 -- KOSOVO-VOICES-2, 3-25 --
The NATO attacks in Yugoslavia prompted a varied reactions around
the U.S. ``It's such a complicated region,'' said Daniel Palladino,
39, left, a television writer. Sidney Verba, 70, a retired state
worker who immigrated from Czechoslovakia after World War II,
expressed doubts about the operation. ``I think it's kind of
stupid,'' he said. ``I'm positive it won't accomplish much. I
wouldn't even dare to guess how it will come out.'' (Kim Kulish/New
York Times Photo)
</P>
