-- BIZ-5-QUESTIONS, 3-25 -- ``The real issues minorities face are
economic,'' not social, says Courtland Cox, head of the Minority
Business Development Agency of the Commerce Department. ``People
try to deal with illegitimacy and crime and drug addiction, but
these are the effects, not the root causes, of problems.'' (New
York Times Photo)
</P>
