Sen. Charles Schumer, D-N.Y., at the Capitol after making his
maiden speech on the floor of the Senate on Thursday. In his
speech, Schumer warned that tensions between New York City's police
force and its minority communities are threatening to undermine the
city's war on crime, and he called on the department to institute
major policy changes to help close the widening rift before it can
``pull us down.'' (Shana Raab/New York Times Photo)
</P>
